author: lundblad
msg: On wc-propcaching branch: Stop setting prop-time field in entries files,
now that we detect property modifications by flag.
NOTE: The low-level entry handling code (including the log code) continues
to support prop-time so that we're able to execute old logs.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/props.c
(svn_wc_props_modified_p): Don't bother "repairing" property timestamp.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/log.c
(log_do_committed): Don't set property timestamp.  Small comment fix.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/adm_ops.c
(revert_admin_things): Don't update property timestamp.  Add TODO reminder.
* subversion/libsvn_wc/update_editor.c
(close_directory): Don't update property timestamp.
(install_file): Don't update property timestamp.  (Give myself a merge
conflict later in the name of not having too many local patches over here:-)

author: dws
msg: Merge r17257 from trunk to 1.3.x branch.
This emits a workaround for bugs in SWIG 1.3.25 and earlier which cause
SWIG_GetModule to be called with the wrong number of arguments.
Required for compatibility with GCC 2.95.x.
Votes:
+1: djames, dberlin, rooneg
